Hi Helena and Rob, a bit late, also here my comments; <@U04M5SGCM5J>: excellent overview of commercial L-sheet options! On our side (The Crick) we have here the Miltenyi-Lavision UMII and we have intensively tested (1 month ago) the Blaze Miltenyi; I could speak for hours regarding both…
Briefly, Lavision UMII: easy and very flexible (large chamber, wide zoom range), but a bit tricky for alignment and high res imaging;
 Blaze: is an improvement (except for the crazy large cuvette) and can be used for multisamples and bigger samples (lenses with higher WD); some improvements in the image quality (flat field of lenses and organization of 3 light-sheet foci;);
 in general, they both still suffer from not very high imaging speed and issues in aligning 6 L-sheets on the same plane; if you need more info, I`ll be happy to set a Zoom meeting (maybe also open to other people?)  and if you want to test the Lavision UMII, you are welcome here in London; or if you have more specific questions, please let me know; hope it helps!
 @ Rob: good to know you have the 3i; we are interested in it as well I`ll be happy to hear your feedback

